<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1047,1326]" box="[151,557,1047,1074]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1047,1074]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1047,1326]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1083,1110]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[668,767,1083,1109]" name="Portugal" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: two northern provinces and Baixo Alentejo in the south in this study, and Algarve (also Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1047,1326]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1156,1182]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from a pasture, an orchard and a montado habitat with 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1194,1156,1182]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis box="[1031,1194,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Quercus suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1229,1328,1155,1181]" name="Portugal" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Medeterinae" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[344,479,1192,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Medetera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diadema">
<emphasis box="[344,479,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">M. diadema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has mainly been found on walls and trunks of deciduous trees in rather dry, grassy biotopes on sandy soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1047,1326]" box="[199,646,1263,1290]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1263,1290]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
3.4 (rare). Fairly rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1047,1326]" box="[199,623,1299,1326]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1299,1326]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Activity period.</emphasis>
September–October.
</paragraph>
